text.config.debugsurvivability.title: Debug World Generation Config
text.config.debugsurvivability.option.gr:
Note on Grid XYZ Size:

By default, Minecraft determines the width and height by finding square root
of total amount of block states (here represented as -1). 
You can put negative numbers to scale that number.
Positive numbers sets the width normally.

text.config.debugsurvivability.option.ba: Which Y level should the barrier floor be.
text.config.debugsurvivability.option.bl:
Which Y level the first block should generate at

If you set it to be the same as barrier level,
 the block will generate inside the floor. 
For survival play, it is suggested for it
to not be under the barrier floor.
